<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-09-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-09-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="835" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d835">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">King of Portugal</gloss> to
                                President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Villa
                                        Vicosa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-09-04"><hi rend="italic">September 4,
                                    1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Have just heard of accident. I express to you my full sympathy and most
                            sincere wishes for your complete recovery.</p>
                        <closer><hi rend="smallcaps">The King of Portugal.</hi></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>